18/02/2005
ATHENS, Greece -- Foreign Ministry spokesman Giorgos Koumoutsakos said on Thursday (17 February) that Greece plans to ratify the EU Constitution before July. He added that the government would not hold a referendum on the document, as demanded by the opposition; instead, it would be debated in parliament only. Koumoutsakos said Greece wants to be among the first EU members to approve the Constitution. (MPA - 17/02/05 
